if you need any restaurant recommendations!'),(2053557,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/2053557','Hilary','I was born and raised in New England and have lived here for most of my life.  I moved to Boston in 1986 and have lived in Central Square, Coolidge Corner and Fort Point; finally settling in Jamaica Plain in 1996.  I am an artist working in primarily textile-based media. I bought my home sixteen years ago and have lovingly renovated it bit by bit ever since.  I am now  lucky to share it with my teenage daughter and our short dog.  If you visit in the warm months you will see I love to garden and if you visit in the winter you will find I bake when I can‚Äôt be outside digging.  Not sitting still for long I am always working on something and my home shows my passions for contemporary ceramics, tools, and the color orange, among other things.  I love where I live and enjoy sharing my house, my collections and my neighborhood with others.'),(2064438,10,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/2064438','Pete','A Boston technology professional who loves traveling, new experiences, and new people! Avid runner and life-long sailor whose big dream is to go on a round-the-world voyage before 40.'),(2100288,15,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/2100288','Anwar',''),(2120544,10,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/2120544','Samuel','Originally from France, I have been living in Boston since 2008. I just renovated my Kitchen, and feel that people might like to stay here instead of a small hotel room. I love my appartment and I like to have people over for diners. \nI am working in Cambridge and walking to work everyday. \nI am personally using airbnb when I travel, as I like to feel home and love cooking. I am keen to let people experience Boston staying in a great neighborhood of Boston.'),(2120816,14,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/2120816','Larry David','Actor/Director/Image Consultant who was involved with the 