o Bruce'),(7825154,29,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/7825154','Ariel','I\'m a university student with a love for traveling! I\'m studying Computer Science and Business at Northeastern University in Boston, and plan to graduate in May 2016.\n\nMost of my time not spent studying is spent working at Yesware, an enterprise software company, on the company\'s Product Management team. In my spare time, I love to walk around the city, try new restaurants, cook with friends, and read about entrepreneurship.'),(7845075,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/7845075','Arnaud','29 years old, French. Engineer, non smoker.'),(7849580,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/7849580','Ann-Marie',''),(7855516,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/7855516','Pamela',''),(7900634,22,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/7900634','Marsha',''),(7912254,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/7912254','Sachin','I enjoy to travel, mostly internationally, I love to meet new people and learn about their experiences. I live in Boston (very centrally located), work for a Healthcare company with a very short commute, which is considered a luxury in Boston, as most people commute several hours a day.'),(7956208,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/7956208','Aida','I have wandered all my life, and I have also traveled; the difference between the two is that we wander for distraction, but we travel for fulfillment.\nTravel is the only thing you buy that makes you richer.'),(7964081,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/7964081','Gabriella','I\'m a criminal justice consultant that travels frequently for work.  I have lived in Boston for 12 years and in the South End for 5 years, and truly enjoy sharing my city and neighborhood with others. I love all things travel, food, and wine related, and have plenty of recommendations!'),(7981083,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/7981083','Dennis','Masters student at MIT'),(7988017,22,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/7988017','Polly',''),(8008692,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8008692','Randy','Professional male living in Boston. I am from MA originally. Spend a lot of my time on the Cape in the summer, and Miami in the Winter. Love the beach and anything outdoors.'),(8012996,29,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8012996','Alice','26 years old clean French couple. No pets and no don\'t smoke.'),(8015347,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8015347','Edwin','I am from West Roxbury MA, I am a Firefighter in Framingham Ma. I aslo own a cottage in Dennis Ma that I rent out year round. I also just joined Airbnb and think its a great way to do business and get to know other people.'),(8023405,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8023405','Artur','I am a young researcher at Harvard med school, spending most of my time at work; I normally stay late at work, unless there is a reason for me to leave earlier, so an early notice is appreciated. Please feel free to email me if you have any questions.\n\nArtur'),(8068253,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8068253','Andrew','I\'m a Boston native. I travel often while working.'),(8104501,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8104501','Annmarie And Earl','We are retired educators, who enjoys traveling, wine, and having fun with family, and friends.\n\nmotto: \"Live, Love, Laugh'),(8130814,30,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8130814','Lison','I am an independent scholar and was a university professor whose fields are French Renaissance Studies and francophone literatures.'),(8139434,30,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8139434','Ari','Hi I look forward to meeting you!\nA little bit about myself and my home:\n\nI am an entrepreneur in my late 20s working on a marketing company. I grow up in Brookline, MA and lived in Boston for most of my life. People who meet me usually take note of my love of helping people.  All my family and friends know I am the \"go to\" if they are in a jam, need advice or if the just need to hang out and have a good time. \n\nI started hosting on Air B&B December 2012 at my previous home.  I recently moved into a new house in August 2013.  I loved my first experience hosting throw Air B&B so much i decided to continue hosting in my new home.  In my new house I have taken hosting to a new level.  Firstly I used my extensive knowledge of Boston to find a home in the most perfect location for all travelers.  Once I found the perfect location I then focused my attention to providing a splendid stay.  I panted every room, brought beautiful furniture, plants, paintings and so much more.  My mission is to provide all of my wonderful guests with a hotel experience while still staying true to the bargain and homey feel of a B&B.  I always strive for perfection and I constantly look for ways of improving my home for my guests.  \n\nI am a true Boston native lived here my hole life.  I know everything Boston so if you have any questions ask away!  I am a big sports fan on Sundays you will find me watching football and everyone is always welcome to join.  I love all kinds of food, which may stem from huge diverse family.  I love working out, running, biking, swimming, yoga and playing sports.  Boston is a very young city and because of that I need to keep myself fit and young in order to keep up with the city.  I love to travel I have been all over the world.  I enjoy camping, grilling, hiking... anything and everything outside.\n\nWhat helps me the most with hosting is my love for people.   Having the ability to provide my guests with a amazing stay in Boston is my #1 goal.'),(8154081,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8154081','Cezanne','I\'m a Nurse Practitioner in Cardiology, a runner, and cyclist. I\'ve lived in Boston for 15 years, but am originally from California. I\'ve shared this space for years with housemates. I like AirBnB for the flexibility, but also because I like meeting new people.\n\nAs for my hosting style- I work a lot and am frequently out with friends.  I\'m of more a hands off person once we get you settled in, but I\'d love to get to know each other over coffee or a glass of wine. I\'m more than happy to supply you with local tips, information, umbrella, etc. at any point in your stay.'),(8157833,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8157833','Dan','Hi there, I am originally from Ireland but have lived in the US for 7 years now. I work in sports and am fortunate enough that it has allowed me to travel all over the world. In my spare time, I love to watch movies, play liars dice, read, and travel at every opportunity. I look forward to having you stay with me here in Boston and sharing my experiences with you!'),(8158181,15,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8158181','Tony','I\'m a young doctor who lives in the unit. My job leaves me little time to spend at home. Love to run and enjoy all types of music.'),(8167936,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8167936','Siqi','Hello!  I\'m an urban designer and researcher, based in Cambridge, Massachusetts.'),(8202984,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8202984','Nathan And Kathryn','We live in Boston and enjoy sharing our New England condo with others. Kathryn is at BU for a PhD and Nathan works in investments. We enjoy racquetball, skiing, SCUBA diving, movies, and music. Kathryn speaks Spanish (Hola) and Nathan speaks Albanian (√á\'kemi).'),(8207666,30,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8207666','Greg',''),(8261931,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8261931','Hamed',''),(8267675,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8267675','Robrecht','I am Belgian and my wife Patricia is from Brazil. We are both living the \'non-resident alien\' life in Boston as a scientist and architect, respectively. Like any good Belgian I like beers, chocolate and french fries, and I think my wife also got the hang of that :-) We both love the good things in life, family, travel, good food, moments together....'),(8295290,45,5,'NY','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8295290','Giuseppe','Hi !\n\nI often travel for work, and I grew up in Belgium, Switzerland, and Boston. \n\nI\'ve hosted more than 150 guests from more than 56 countries - if you have any questions don\'t hesitate to reach out - look forward to hosting you !\n\nGiuseppe'),(8302344,1,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8302344','Dan','I am very outdoors oriented and love spending time in nature in all seasons.  I also enjoy activities with my girlfriend Liz and 10 year old daughter Amelia.  We are big campers and kayakers.  Rainy days will find us reading aloud to each other, playing bananagrams or watching a movie.  We are all artists and love drawing, coloring, crafting.   Recently we have taken up stone balancing as our favorite beach activity. \n\nI also host on Air BnB in my Boston home.  As I once travelled the world, AirBnB is a way I can give back to those who are more fleet of foot than I am now.  I love hearing about ways of life far from here in Boston, and sharing the inside scoop on destinations around town. \n\nIf I had to name my life motto....Seize the Twinkie!'),(8408214,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8408214','Sarah','Bonjour a tous,\n\nMy name is Sarah, I was born in Morocco and have been a Bostonian for the past seven years. Prior to date, I lived and studied in France for seven years.\n\nMy childhood in Morocco taught me Arabic, French, empathy, respect, resourcefulness, flexibility and quick problem solving skills.\n\nMy parents gave me their thirst for learning and continuous improvement, their professionalism, work ethic and dedication.\n\nMy seven years in France sharpened my taste in European pastry, Caribbean music and fed my general knowledge.\n\nMy seven years so far in the US awakened my passion for running and thrift shopping.\n\nNow ? I am :\n\n- making my way in the fascinating world of Non Profit Project Management.\n- running 10k every two days.\n- learning Spanish.\n- reading every book I can find by Marcel Rufin.\n- watching religiously Suits every Thursday and Ballers every Sunday.\n\nMy husband and I have been using Airbnb as guests for the past 2 years and started hosting ourselves on August 2015. We are multilingual, curious about every other culture and traveling is basically a second nature (as much as an addiction).\n\nLooking forward to meet you as guest or host (or who knows, maybe both).\n\nWarm regards,\n\nSarah.'),(8479265,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8479265','Alejandro','A fun bartender  from Boston who obviously loves mixing drinks, cooking, eating out, traveling and enjoying life'),(8491165,1,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8491165','Jeff','Hi, I am Jeff and my wife is Katie. I am a full-time student at UMass Boston studying for a master\'s degree in Global Inclusion and Social Development, and I also work full-time for the Veterans Administration. Katie is a paralegal working in family law downtown. We enjoy spending time with our two dogs (Nutmeg& Teddy), so if you don\'t like dogs, you should not request this room. They are friendly, but won\'t bother you much accept for greeting you at the door. Also, we like baseball (Red Sox fans) and football, politics (we are progressive Democrats), travelling, reading, and just hanging out in our living room. Some of the places we have traveled to are Malaysia, Mexico, Netherlands, San Francisco, Puerto Rico, New Orleans, Jamaica, Texas, and New York City. I am also a veteran and spent a year in Afghanistan. We are both very laid back, and welcome the same type of folks. I grew up in southeastern Mass, and Katie is from Houston, Texas. Come check out the place and our city. We have plenty of room.'),(8498315,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8498315','Joe/Ayad','I work in Real Estate and my partner is a Harvard Physician practicing in Boston. We have two well traveled French bulldogs (Biscuit and Roux) that we include when we can. We prefer quiet places to stay with clean conditions and accurately represented properties.  We greatly respect the Airbnb process, the folks offering lodging,  and the folks wanting to rent our Airbnb space.'),(8503981,30,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8503981','Elham',''),(8573721,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8573721','Razan','Hello, I am Razan.'),(8582699,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8582699','Poppy','Born in Jakarta, raised in Bali, I spend most of my adult live in the US. Currently living and working in Boston. I love traveling and enjoy meeting people, making new friends and learning about different cultures.'),(8625838,22,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8625838','David',''),(8654826,30,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8654826','Michael','Boston, MA!'),(8725557,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8725557','Brooke','Young professional willing looking to host guests in a great location.'),(8739837,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8739837','Ada','I enjoy traveling, sailing and learning about new cultures.  I work in business development for a Boston firm, but at heart I\'m a historian with an interest in grand empires and world societies.  I think Boston is one of the best cities in the world, offering a metropolitan culture, and yet being within an hour away from beautiful New England beaches and grandiose mountains.  (few places can offer all three in such close proximity :) )'),(8790904,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8790904','Albert','I\'m originally from New York but am living in the South End/Back Bay neighborhood of Boston. I\'m clean, organized and neat. The various cleaning robots I have in my apartment will attest to that!\n\nHope to have some interesting adventures and hope you will as well!'),(8792144,13,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8792144','Rachel','Originally from Boston (Rachel) & Portland, ME (Nate), we live upstairs from the unit, and have quickly fallen in love with Charlestown and all it has to offer!  We are here for any questions you might have :)'),(8793032,30,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8793032','Justan','I am from Milan, Italy and love to travel.'),(8812693,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8812693','Cornelia',''),(8814724,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8814724','Kelly','We\'re Kelly, Phil, and Campbell (our 9-year old son).  We love living in our JP neighborhood, walking to parks, riding bikes, geo caching, and drinking great coffee!  When we\'re not in JP, we\'re in the mountains or exploring remote parts of the world.  Come visit!!'),(8829183,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8829183','Eran','We are nice, clean and friendly couple from Boston. We are both PhD student at Boston University and MIT.'),(8834105,1,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8834105','Rebecca','Bon Jour, Bom Dia, Good Day,\n\nI\'m a mid-life psychologist who enjoys traveling and the hospitality and connections that come with it. I am happy to have the opportunity to make you welcome. I do have a full life, so we may have less time to converse than I\'d like, but I am happy to do what I can to make your stay comfortable.\n\nI was born here but I\'m half Portuguese (and used to speak good conversational French a while ago - I can probably do okay with French visitors who don\'t speak the best English), so hospitality is one of my cultural values. \n\nI also have a garden, good neighbors, cats, and enjoy good food and warm people.'),(8879967,1,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8879967','Joanne','Born on a ranch in Nevada and now a resident of New England for the past thirty five years. I\'m a shop owner where I am the purveyor of the unnecessary and irresistible! I have a sassy sense of humor and great taste in decorating.'),(8881643,10,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8881643','David',''),(8898897,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8898897','Taylor',''),(8898973,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8898973','Adriana & Gianni','Friendly,responsible and profesional.'),(8907338,29,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8907338','Abhay',''),(8924578,15,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8924578','Matteo','Entrepreneur and Attorney. I move around a lot but truly appreciate living in Beacon Hill and all it has to offer.'),(8985714,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8985714','Tj','I live in South Boston, but travel frequently for both work and pleasure - well, it\'s always pleasure, but sometimes work pays for it.  I have used Airbnb in several countries and cities and have had fantastic experiences while meeting some great people along the way.  I am now just starting to offer my own condo to like-minded travelers looking for an affordable, convenient place to stay.'),(8992252,10,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/8992252','Laurel',''),(9039817,3,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/9039817','Jeremy',''),(9046262,8,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/9046262','Andrei',''),(9073339,12,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/9073339','Elisangela','I am  an entrepreneur and a Professional artist.  I love meeting new people and  having people over my home. It gives me joy to make you feel special. Before you come in I make sure that everything looks just about perfect to have you.  I always try to meet you in person if my schedule permits to  welcome you with a big smile. I will treat you and respect like my own family. I enjoy traveling a lot and  I