 interests. And I\'d love to have you return again and again.'),(15892865,15,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/15892865','Michael','I travel for work a lot, and I love exploring new places. I work for a startup company in New York City, and I am the Director of our custom solutions team. My job is to take interesting data and build cool stuff with it with cool people. \n\nI am a graduate of Colgate University, and I am originally from New Jersey. I now live in New York. \n\nIn my free time, I\'m a big reader. My favorite authors are Malcolm Gladwell and Michael Lewis. I\'m a huge baseball fan and a bigtime history geek.'),(16044270,10,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16044270','Sarah',''),(16052189,20,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16052189','Jonathan','Living in the Boston area. Like to stay busy after work. Professional dance instructor, entrepreneur and always active. Relaxed personality that likes to have fun.'),(16059043,22,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16059043','Veronika','I am 1st generation American from European decsent. I love people from all walks of life, and believe that we all have much to teach and learn from one another! I have traveled the world (not as much as I would have liked to), and still am in love with Italy. I love the outdoors and spend time hiking with my dog Dallas. Food is my other pleasure, and not a lot of it just really clean and delicious!  Horseback riding is my therapy for everything. I am full of life and good energy!!  \"The most beautiful things in life are not seen but felt by the heart and soul\"  Helen Keller'),(16067950,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16067950','Moshe','My name is Moshe I live in ma love to read books love to travel and enjoying music just came back few weeks ago from jazz festival on Montreal next trip is with my youngest child 16 to Alaska .\nI like to host and I\'m doing it . \nI\'m an easy going guest I like clean cozy places and most important nice host,that\'s what\'s  given  the place is unique .\nThanks'),(16154941,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16154941','Kayla',''),(16186589,22,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16186589','Marie','I am a Property Manager'),(16284736,12,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16284736','Jordan','I\'m a recent law school grad who works from home half the month, and travels the other half.  I spend time searching for hidden gem eateries, jogging around the city, and catching up on my HBO. \n\nClean, respectful, and always happy to host a new friend.'),(16330682,3,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16330682','Evan',''),(16337422,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16337422','Orion','Hannah, our children and I really enjoy picking strawberries, raspberries and grapes in our garden. We like the urban lifestyle, taking the T, walking down the block to visit friends, shopping at the local farmers market, and hosting BBQs in our community orchard. And when we can get out of the city to camp, go to the beach, or hike we do! \n\nI am a Boston native with a good knowledge of the city and the local neighborhood. My work has taken me around the world meeting people from many different countries and we\'ve hosted friends and colleagues from South Africa, England, Cuba, and more locally from the US. My wife Hannah is English and has also done extensive traveling. She speaks French and Spanish, and I also speak Spanish from living for a few years in Guatemala. Last year we went to Iceland and stayed in Airbnbs and had a great time, so we hope we can give you as much hospitality as we received!'),(16343599,1,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16343599','Ella & Will','We are from the UK and working our way around the world. We have been lucky enough to live  in some great cities; London, Tokyo, New York and Boston. We\'re trying to take in every state while we are here in the US. We\'ve also enjoyed destinations from Burma to Belize. All before the advent of AirBnb unfortunately....\n\nThese days our travel consists largely of journeys north to fix up a farmhouse in Maine and trips back to the UK to take the kids to see the grandparents. We are enjoying bringing the world to Boston through AirBnb, and satisfying some wanderlust by being good hosts! We are happy to introduce you to this leafy green corner of the city. We are also wannabe Mainers. So if you plan a New England tour, we\'d be happy to share our tips.\n\nWe recognize that travel is precious family/free time. We want you to be comfortable. I\'d describe our hosting style as \"friendly, but not hovering\".'),(16375951,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16375951','Bec','I am a teacher heading on a cross-country road trip for the summer. It seems like a shame for my great apartment to go to waste - especially during the best time of the year in Boston!'),(16379445,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16379445','Kelly','I\'m a tax lawyer by trade who loves to take dance classes, be outside, and invest in my community.  My husband is a chaplain at Harvard University who loves to watch cricket, meet new people, and run marathons (who really loves that?).  We\'re newly weds who enjoy staying in Airbnb homes when we travel and like opening our home through Airbnb to travelers too!'),(16398126,1,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16398126','Chris','Laid back guy who enjoys seeing new parts of the country and learning about them, hiking, craft beers, museums, and meeting new folks.'),(16442921,22,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16442921','Orchid','I enjoy meeting people from around the world and welcome them to Boston .'),(16492238,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16492238','Farouk',''),(16522894,10,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/16522894','Anna','Hello!  Welcome to my hosting page :)\n\nI\'m a young professional