te winter activity is skiing.  Also love a good cup of coffee (black, no cream or sugar).'),(20399668,22,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20399668','Ananya',''),(20434629,29,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20434629','E‚ÄÜRic','I\'m a student from northeastern university'),(20436793,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20436793','Diana',''),(20447366,22,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20447366','Jason','Hey! I\'m just a regular guy living in Boston. I work a ton, and spend my off time traveling the world. There is nothing better than traveling, and meeting new people. I don\'t really have a favorite destination... even though I have done my share of traveling. \n\nThanks for checking out my profile!'),(20454595,9,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20454595','Margarita',''),(20515798,3,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20515798','Isaac',''),(20582119,39,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20582119','Jeff','We enjoy helping travelers to Boston have outstanding experiences by providing some of the best accommodations in the City, offering curated local guidance, and maintaining a high service level for our guests.  We are available to help, but we also aim to be unobtrusive.  We look forward to hosting you!'),(20598985,20,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20598985','Carlotta','Our family is  proud to be welcome you into our home, our friends and family recognize us for  our enduring values, our spirit to serve, and our commitment to creating  a better places to visit, relax  and work.'),(20627610,10,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20627610','Liri','I\'m a holistic nutrition coach and doula, who is also passionate about real estate, design, yoga, cooking and travel. I spend about half the year in Tel Aviv (Israel) with family. Checkout my blog for healthy recipes: \nwww Zestilicious com\n\nThe business school at Boston University brought me to Boston many years ago, but the charm of the city kept me here. I would love for you to feel at home while you visit \'Casa Waltham\' so please reach out if you have any questions or requests for recommendations!'),(20684898,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20684898','Vanessa',''),(20733420,13,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20733420','Roger',''),(20823261,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20823261','Kevin',''),(20857768,39,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20857768','Adam','My name is Adam and I am a Sales Representative for Compass Furnished Apartments. We offer short-term and long-term fully furnished, fully equipped apartments in the Northeastern United States. \n\nOur comfortable homes, streamlined reservation process and ‚Äúconcierge-style‚Äù client services enable us to provide our guests with an exceptional experience, all at a tremendous value.\n\nOur forward looking approach to technology and sustainable business practices coupled with our experience in evaluating and fulfilling the specific needs of every client lead many to choose Compass for their furnished apartment needs.'),(20907980,15,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20907980','Jay','New Yorker / Californian in Boston. Researcher at MIT messing with technology to fix urban transportation.'),(20912254,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20912254','Liz And Dale','We are artists, dancers, travelers, and city dwellers who love good people, good music, good food, & good stories - be it movie, book, tv or other. We love Boston and especially living in JP because of its diversity, culture, walkability, public transportation and proximity to downtown Boston.\n\nWe travel all kinds of ways from staying in homes to resorts and appreciate the perks of each. What we love the most about this method of travel is having a base to kick back between excursions and have a snack or breakfast at \"home\" to save a bit of money and calories for the next meal!\n\nAs hosts, we keep our place in great condition so you can have a comfortable stay. We want the space to be enjoyed and its important to us that our guests leave happy!'),(20915681,8,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20915681','Brad','I\'m a young professional in the high-tech space, who appreciates great design and the great outdoors. When I\'m not traveling, camping, or skiing, I run marketing for a cloud computing company in Boston. \n\nI\'m from Colorado, went to school in North Carolina, and have been in Boston for 5 years. Two fun facts about me are that I\'ve played tennis on every continent except Antarctica and build my own wood furniture.'),(20931226,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20931226','Tai',''),(20934696,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/20934696','Stephanie','I work for a technology company Just outside of Boston and often find myself traveling for conferences and clients. I always try to balance work and fun with each place that I am venturing to!'),(21009959,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/21009959','Drew','We are two hospitality professionals looking to welcome you to Boston! When we\'re not in the restaurant, you\'ll find us cooking up a storm and having friends over for dinner and nice wine; so hosting Airbnb guests come naturally to us.'),(21021264,6,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/21021264','Judy',''),(21093140,22,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/21093140','Paul And Lauren','Paul and his wife, Lauren, spend the summer in the cape and would love to rent their place to you! Flexible with dates, just ask! You can learn more about us by visiting Lauren\'s blog >> (URL HIDDEN)'),(21094197,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/21094197','James',''),(21149134,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/21149134','Johanna',''),(21184200,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/21184200','Paige','