ocation to get anywhere. I probably won\'t be there, but a wonderful person will be there to meet you and make sure you are all taken care of.  I can always be reached by phone.  I love to visit new cities!'),(28564205,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28564205','Aanchal',''),(28617972,52,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28617972','John',''),(28657432,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28657432','Edi',''),(28662210,3,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28662210','Terry',''),(28662502,15,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28662502','Tiffany','Originally from New Hampshire, I live/work in Boston, and spend most of my free time enjoying nature, my dog Gizmo, and sightseeing the beautiful city I live in! I\'m really into food so if you ever need any recommendations for places to eat in Boston, I\'m here to help :)'),(28749942,28,4,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28749942','Fernanda','Brazilian, living in Boston. I\'m Passionate about travel and meeting people from around the world. Spanish, English and Portuguese speaker.'),(28759412,13,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28759412','Jayme',''),(28763698,14,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28763698','Eleanore',''),(28766987,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28766987','Kathy','Born in Michigan, started working in Houston in 1997 and never really left.  Since 2002, we have lived in our house in central Houston in a part of Houston (Montrose) that is now too hip for us.  Two girls, 6&8, and 1 dog (Lili).\n  \nI had my first Airbnb experience in 2015 and it was perfect.  How do I know?  My little one started crying as we pulled out of the driveway.\n\nThe Boston apartment is meant to be for family visits, but it\'s in an amazing location, so might as well let others use them to enjoy the city. \n\nWe usually take 1 big trip / year.  Our other travels are to family commitments in Michigan, Chicago, or Boston, or our annual get-together with the uncle and grandparents for Thanksgiving in Florida.  We love traveling.  I have lived in Russia, Ukraine, and France and visit occasionally (went to Ukraine in May).  My husband spent part of his child/teenage years in Spain.  The girls are entering 1st and 3rd grade in a Mandarin Immersion school.  Our dog only barks in American English, though.'),(28820575,9,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28820575','S.P.','We are a Property Management provider of Premium Rooms in the Boston area. We deal only in excellency. We are comprised of family oriented individuals who strive for the best experience for you. If there is an issue with any of our properties or rooms, We will personally address the issue if need be. People and relationships is what matters. YOU Matter!!!'),(28880663,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28880663','Amanda','Florida native that fell in love with Boston 4 years ago and hasn\'t left since! \n\nI\'m a young professional, work downtown, and being from the south I\'ve had tons of friends come visit, so plenty of opportunities to explore my new city.\n\nI travel, explore, and eat ... a lot.  Life\'s about experiences!'),(28943553,10,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28943553','Tessa',''),(28972872,10,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28972872','Marc','We are quiet professionals who love to travel and experience different cultures. Marc\'s background is as an entrepreneur and consultant. Stephanie is pursuing her passion as an editor. Because our work can often be done remotely, we can travel around while still working. This makes Airbnb a wonderful concept for us. We have traveled and lived all over Europe but have decided to settle in Boston because it\'s such a wonderful city. Marc is an avid runner, snowboarder and cook. Stephanie is also an avid cook, and she\'s happiest curled up reading a book or sipping a glass of wine.'),(28974969,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28974969','Jennifer','Sorry I have few reviews so far, I\'m brand new to Airbnb! \n\nI have my Masters in Biomedical Science and work in the Boston area. I love traveling, hosting and meeting new people! I\'m proud of my place and would love to share with you all I know about the area.'),(28975718,2,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28975718','Thomas',''),(28980127,11,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28980127','Al','Living and working in Boston. Love all sort of sport activities, dinning, travelling and nature.'),(28985064,24,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/28985064','Christina',''),(29025144,10,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29025144','Jay','I am a 26-year old living in Boston for the past 8 years. I usually travel with friends for hanging out or exploring.'),(29066313,30,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29066313','Andy','I\'m a teacher and learner by trade.  I\'m fascinated with learning about people and the cultures they come from, especially the foods of different cultures.  My family has worked in the restaurant business for many years and food and the stories and people behind the food are things that make everyday life exciting.  I enjoy many of the local conventions as well and consider myself deeply immersed in the Geek culture so PaxEast, ComicCon, Boston Anime convention goers are welcome here.  A long time Boston Native I love cheering on the local teams, the Red Sox, The Bruins, The Celtics and especially the Pats.'),(29112750,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29112750','Rosie',''),(29187425,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29187425','Olja',''),(29224952,30,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29224952','Shoshana',''),(29227463,29,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29227463','Dylan','Hi!\n\nI\'m originally from Connecticut, but travel frequently to New York and Boston. Currently working in downtown Boston, I went to Northeastern University with a major in finance and entrepreneurship. \n\nAs a host I will do everything possible to make your stay the most pleasant. Any questions or concerns I will address immediately. Your satisfaction is guaranteed.'),(29336905,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29336905','Emily',''),(29385474,8,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29385474','Justin','I\'m from Boston and I run a software company called BeaconsInSpace. We work with mobile apps and bluetooth devices called iBeacons. We\'ve been at it for a year and a half, and things have been going well- very exciting!\n\nWhen I\'m not busy working on my company, I do standup comedy on the side.'),(29394026,30,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29394026','Leyla','26 years old female, student.'),(29407427,30,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29407427','Gizem',''),(29472153,13,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29472153','Kristin','My name is Kristin and I live by myself in a large apartment in Charlestown. I travel often for work and pleasure and my apartment is often left open. I would love for people to get to experience Charlestown like I do. I love my neighbors and our friendly community located in the Navy Yard is a great spot!  I promise you will fall in love with Charlestown and the great location of being on the water!'),(29483150,52,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29483150','Irida','Energetic European :) living in Boston for quite a while. My money is spend traveling & exploring excellent little neighborhood places & great food. \nI speak fluent Italian & English.'),(29503737,15,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29503737','Victoria',''),(29531596,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29531596','Marcus',''),(29537980,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/29537980','Alyssa',''),(29568033,15,1,'MA','US','https://www.airbnb.com